A keyed-hash message authentication code (hmac) library for ruby
	
this library provides hmac functionality with ruby. hmac is a type of "message
authentication code" (mac) algorithm documented in rfc2104, which is used to
verify integrity of data transmitted over or stored in unreliable medium,
based on a secret key.

this is a dependency package which depends on debian's default ruby version
(currently 1.8.x).